{{Infobox protected area | name = Campos del Tuyú National Park | alt_name = Parque Nacional Campos del Tuyú | iucn_category = II | photo = Atardecer en Campos del Tuyú.jpg | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Parque Nacional Campos del Tuyú | photo_width = | map = Argentina | relief = 1 | map_alt = | map_caption = | map_width = 150 | location = [[Buenos Aires Province]], Argentina | nearest_city = | coords = {{coord|36|21|S|56|52|W|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = | area = {{Convert|3040|ha|acre}} | established = 2009 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = | url = }} '''Campos del Tuyú National Park''' ({{lang-es|Parque Nacional Campos del Tuyú}}) is a [[National parks of Argentina|national park]] in [[Buenos Aires Province]], [[Argentina]]. Situated on the southern shore of [[Samborombón Bay]], the park was established on May 13, 2009.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Parque Nacional Campos del Tuyú|website=Administración de Parques Nacionales de Argentina|language=Spanish|url=https://www.sib.gov.ar/area/APN*CT*Campos%20del%20Tuy%C3%BA|accessdate=17 July 2017}}</ref> The main attraction of Campos del Tuyú is the rare [[pampas deer]]; in fact, it is one of the few places in the [[Pampas]] where this species survive. Other inhabitants of the park include over a hundred bird species, [[capybara]], and the likewise endangered [[Leopardus geoffroyi]].
