{{Infobox power station | name = Lomi Power Station | name_official = ''Lomi kraftverk'' | image = Lomi kraftverk.jpg | location_map = Nordland | location_map_caption = Location in [[Nordland]] county | coordinates = {{coord|67|07|26|N|16|05|49|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | location = [[Sulitjelma]], [[Nordland]] | country = Norway | status = O | construction_began = | commissioned = {{Start date and age|1979}} | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = [[Salten Kraftsamband]] | operator = | psps_upper_res = Låmivatnet | psps_upper_res_capacity= | psps_penstocks = | psps_lower_res = | psps_lower_res_capacity= | psps_hydraulic_head = 580&nbsp;m | psps_generators = 2 | psps_pumpgenerators = | psps_pumps = | ps_units_operational = | ps_units_manu_model = [[Francis turbine]] | ps_units_uc = | ps_units_planned = | ps_units_cancelled = | ps_units_decommissioned= | ps_electrical_capacity = 120 | ps_electrical_cap_fac = 34.5%<!-- 362,000 MWh/year / ( 120 MW * 365 days/year * 24h/day) = 0.345 --> | ps_annual_generation = 362 | ps_annual_gen_year = | website = | extra = }}
The '''Lomi Hydroelectric Power Station''' ({{lang-no|Lomi kraftverk}} or ''Lomi kraftstasjon''<ref name="Sks">[https://www.sks.no/produksjon/kraftstasjoner/lomi/ SKS produksjon: Lomi.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202005059/https://www.sks.no/produksjon/kraftstasjoner/lomi/ |date=2017-02-02 }}</ref>) is a [[hydroelectricity|hydroelectric]] [[power station]] in the municipality of [[Fauske]] in [[Nordland]] [[Counties of Norway|county]], [[Norway]].<ref>[http://publikasjoner.nve.no/publikasjonV/publikasjonV_32.pdf Norges Vassdrags- og Energiverk (NVE). 2016. ''Utbygd vannkraft i Norge pr. 01.01.1990.'' Oslo, p. 42.]</ref> It utilizes a drop of {{convert|580|m|sp=us}}<ref name="Sks"/> between its intake reservoir on ''[[Låmivatnet]]'' (Lake Låmi; also {{lang-no|Lomivatnet}}<ref name="yr1">{{cite web|url=https://www.yr.no/place/Norway/Nordland/Fauske/L%C3%A5mivatnet/|title=Låmivatnet, Fauske (Nordland)|publisher=[[yr.no]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=January 22, 2017}}</ref><ref>[http://www.ranablad.no/sulitjelma/redningsaksjon/nordland/to-svenske-kvinner-ma-berges-med-sea-king/s/5-42-83626 Johansen, Øyvind. 2015. To svenske kvinner må berges med Sea King. ''Ranablad'' (August 5).]</ref> {{lang-smj|Loamejávrre}}<ref name="yr1"/>), which can be regulated at a level between {{cvt|708|m}} and {{cvt|649|m}}. The reservoir is supplied by water from ''Storelvvatnan'' ({{lang-smj|Duolldagåpjávrre}}<ref name="yr2">{{cite web|url=https://www.yr.no/place/Norway/Nordland/Fauske/Storelvvatnan/|title=Storelvvatnan, Fauske (Nordland)|publisher=[[yr.no]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=January 22, 2017}}</ref>), a lake regulated at a level between {{cvt|798|m}} and {{cvt|792|m}}, and also by some stream intakes. Part of the water supplying the plant is runoff from the [[Sulitjelma Glacier]]. The plant has two [[Francis turbine]]s and operates at an installed capacity of {{nowrap|120 [[Megawatt|MW]]}}, with an average annual production of about 362&nbsp;GWh.<ref name="Sks"/> Its total catchment area is {{convert|145|km2|sp=us}}. The plant is owned by [[Salten Kraftsamband]] and came into operation in 1979.<ref name="Sks"/> The water is reused by the [[Sjønstå Hydroelectric Power Station]] further downstream in the [[Sulitjelma drainage system]].
