{{Infobox Doll | title = Wooden doll of Natungram | image = কাঠের_পেঁচা,_নতুনগ্রাম_পশ্চিমবঙ্গ.jpg | image_size = | caption = '''Colored Wooden Owl''' | origin‌‌_place = [[Notungram]], [[West Bengal]], [[India]] | origin‌‌_date = | created_by = | creation_date = | ingredients = Wood and colors | shape = Mummy Shape | height = | colour = Various colors | style = | usage = Decorating | related_festival = | variants = Owl, Gour NItai, Jagannath | related_dolls = | manufacturer = | distributor = | gi_status = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }} {{commons category|Wooden dolls}} '''Wooden Dolls of Natungram''' is very popular in [[West Bengal]] and also in [[India]]. The art-making wooden dolls have been an age-old practice in India and Natungram is one of them. It situated in [[Burdwan district]] of [[West Bengal]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://toureast.in/destination/natungram/|title=Natungram: A place for Cultural tourism of rural Bengal|website=toureast.in|language=en-US|access-date=2018-01-25}}</ref> There are many kinds of dolls like Gour-Nitai, Wooden owl, Krishna, Royal couple etc. The wooden owl is most popular among them.
==History== [[File:কাঠের পেঁচা, নতুনগ্রাম.jpg|thumb|Wooden owl, Natungram]] The artist of Natungram used to work in stone carving first. with the king's patronage, they were working well. But after the fall of the king of Bardhaman, the craftsmen face difficulties. Then they left the stone carving industry and started doing fine arts and wooden works. One of the common family names here is '''''[[Sutradhar]]''''' because inspirations for most dolls are drawn from mythologies and folklore.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://seemaawasthiblog.wordpress.com/2016/08/06/natungram-of-bardhaman-district-is-the-hub-for-wooden-doll-making-in-west-bengal/|title=Natungram of Bardhaman district is the hub for wooden doll making in West Bengal.|date=2016-08-06|work=Hand Made Toys|access-date=2018-01-25|language=en-US}}</ref>
==Method== [[File:কাঠের পুতুল নতুনগ্রাম.jpg|thumb|Wooden dolls, Natungram]] Dolls are mainly made out of Gamar wood, Mango wood, Shimul wood, Ata wood, Chatim wood.<ref>https://www.ijhsss.com/files/Agnimitra-Majumder.pdf</ref> After making a shape of dolls, men carved the wood as per the requirement. Then women have painted the products with various colour. Then they used a glue, made from tamarind seed. Colouring has to be done by the female member of a family. They have used lots of colours in the dolls like white, green, yellow, black borders and red.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://souradeep141905.blogspot.in/|title=Wooden Dolls of Natungram|website=souradeep141905.blogspot.in|access-date=2018-01-25}}</ref>
